https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/specs/man/java.html
-XX:ObjectAlignmentInBytes=alignment

Enables or disable the use of compressed pointers (object references represented as 32 bit offsets instead of 64-bit pointers) for optimized 64-bit performance with Java heap sizes less than 32gb.
-XX:-UseCompressedOops (disable)  -XX:+UseCompressedOops enable

